LLM-ready patch: Gate ConnectivityBadge by feature flag and avoid starting network when disabled

Target file: components/offline/connectivity-badge.tsx

1) Add feature flag import
Insert at top after existing imports:
  import { getFeatureFlag } from '@/lib/offline/feature-flags'

2) Short-circuit render when flag is OFF
At the start of the component function (after hooks), add:
  const flagEnabled = getFeatureFlag('offline.circuitBreaker')
  if (!flagEnabled) return null

3) Only start network service when flag is ON
In the useEffect where networkService.start() is called, wrap it:
  // Start network service
  if (getFeatureFlag('offline.circuitBreaker')) {
    networkService.start();
  }

Notes:
- networkService.start() already checks the flag, but this avoids any setup and renders no badge when disabled.
